column5: Get up, eat breakfast, shower, brush teeth, etc. Then either go to classes or work on my laptop in bed or in my office. During that time if I'm working on projects from home I usually get distracted a few times by scrolling on reddit or watching youtube. If i'm in classes and don't have any in-person meetings after, I get home around 2pm and take the dogs out and then make lunch with some youtube and maybe get some more homework done till dinnner. Otherwise if I stay on campus I eat a packed lunch along with some youtube. Finish up the day with project work on campus (usually with a friend or groupmates). If I have classes on both campuses that day I bike between them. Come home, eat dinner with family (if schedules align), and then either continue project work or play video games with friends. Sleeep.
